 President of the National Industrial Court of Nigeria (NICN), Justice Babatunde Adejumo, has said that the inauguration of the Benin Division of the NICN will provide respite for individuals and organisations in Edo state involved in the over 300 pending industrial disputes emanating from the state. Continue reading Respite as Industrial Court in Benin set to address over 300 pending industrial disputes in Edo at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard